{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ba7a5042-0c0b-487d-8ef8-53e5a8384cf1","content":"Here are the issues I found:\n\n1. **Missing `identity`** — Required field for .NET templates; uniquely identifies the template.\n\n2. **`shortName: \"restore\"`** — Conflicts with the built-in `dotnet restore` command.\n\n3. **`targetFramework` default `\"net7.0\"`** — Not one of the defined choices (`net8.0`, `net9.0`).\n\n4. **`maxRetries` default `\"abc\"`** — Invalid for `datatype: \"int\"`.\n\n5. **`computed1` missing `value`** — Computed symbols require a `value` expression.\n\n6. **`generated1` missing `generator`** — Generated symbols require a `generator` property.\n\n7. **`postActions` entry missing `actionId`** — Each post-action needs an `actionId` (GUID) to specify the action type.\n\nItems 1, 3–7 will cause runtime errors or undefined behavior. Item 2 will shadow a core CLI command.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8cc1090e-bd5f-4f48-9ae2-678008777928","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me analyze this template.json for issues:\n\n1. **Missing `identity`** - The `identity` field is required in .NET template.json files. It should be a unique identifier for the template.\n\n2. **`shortName: \"restore\"`** - \"restore\" is a reserved dotnet CLI command. Using it as a shortName will conflict with `dotnet restore`.\n\n3. **`defaultValue: \"net7.0\"` for `targetFramework`** - The default value is \"net7.0\", but the available choices only include \"net8.0\" and \"net9.0\". The default value should be one of the available choices.\n\n\n4. **`defaultValue: \"yes\"` for `enableLogging`** - For a bool parameter, the standard convention is to use `\"true\"` or `\"false\"` rather than `\"yes\"`, though the template engine does technically accept both formats.\n\n5. **`defaultValue: \"abc\"` for `maxRetries`** - This is invalid since `maxRetries` is an integer and \"abc\" can't be parsed as a number.\n\n6. **`computed1` missing `value`** - Computed symbols need a `value` property with a C++ style boolean expression.\n\n7. **`generated1` missing `generator`** - Generated symbols require a `generator` property to specify which generator to use.\n\n8. **`postActions` entry missing `actionId`** - Post actions need an `actionId` (a GUID) to identify which action to run.\n\n9. **Missing `sourceName`** - While not strictly required, this is commonly expected.\n\n10. **Missing `$schema`** - Recommended but not required.\n\nThe core issues are the missing `identity` field and the conflicting `shortName: \"restore\"` entries.","outputTokens":902,"requestId":"A7CD:36C28E:15F729F:188E48C:6A051F53"},"id":"c9e56035-f105-4d32-afc3-f6ade6a28a93","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:03:31.769Z","parentId":"1bc6d97b-0bfa-4b3f-9e09-e10820fa1c75"}
